Caribbean coral reefs are threatened by rising seas

Modelling suggests that most Caribbean coral reefs will erode by the year 2100 as sea-level rise outpaces reef growth and limits potential reef restoration.





                By

Nicola K. Browne ORCID: http://orcid.org/0000-0002-7160-68650

Nicola K. Browne




                            Nicola K. Browne is at the School of the Environment, University of Queensland, Brisbane, Queensland 4072, Australia. 






                            View author publications


                                    Search author on:
                                    PubMed
                                     Google Scholar

Twitter





